262
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,890
- We did?
- Who's that?

263
00:12:21,182 --> 00:12:23,811
- It's Booth.
- No, no, no, before it was you.

264
00:12:23,936 --> 00:12:26,036
Booth, you pressed "conference."

265
00:12:26,204 --> 00:12:28,215
- It's me Booth.
- Booth is on painkillers.

266
00:12:28,340 --> 00:12:30,063
Is the victim's father coming in?

267
00:12:30,188 --> 00:12:32,000
- I want to be there.
- No, you can't.

268
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:34,002
- He can't.
- Why?

269
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,355
Yes, I can.

270
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,316
What are you still doing
on this call?

271
00:12:37,441 --> 00:12:40,011
No, Agent Perotta,
his back is very bad.

272
00:12:40,136 --> 00:12:41,429
He can't be there.

273
00:12:41,554 --> 00:12:43,053
You can't let him in.

274
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:45,537
Yes, I can.
I am the ranking officer.

275
00:12:45,662 --> 00:12:48,183
But you are incapacitated
by painkillers.

276
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:50,544
Bones, enough, okay?
I'm not incapacapitated,

277
00:12:50,669 --> 00:12:52,519
whatever you said there,
all right? I just...

278
00:12:52,644 --> 00:12:54,528
Don't listen to her, Perotta.
Don't.

279
00:12:57,446 --> 00:12:59,749
Did you daughter
live at home with you, Mr. Kim?

280
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:01,375
No.

281
00:13:01,993 --> 00:13:04,324
No. Kendra lived
in a condo in Logan Circle.

282
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:07,202
Look, ask him when was the last time
he saw his daughter.

283
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:10,738
- What was that?
- This is Agent, Booth.

284
00:13:10,863 --> 00:13:11,623
Hello?

285
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:14,401
He's unable to be with us in person.

286
00:13:15,591 --> 00:13:17,644
Kendra and I didn't see
each other much,

287
00:13:17,769 --> 00:13:20,330
despite the fact
that I put a roof over her head.

288
00:13:20,455 --> 00:13:22,683
According to the modeling agency
that booked your daughter,

289
00:13:22,808 --> 00:13:24,648
all of her checks were sent
to your address.

290
00:13:24,773 --> 00:13:27,931
The money went to pay the mortgage
on the condo, which is also in my name.

291
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:30,475
It's kind of a weird arrangement,
now isn't it?

292
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:31,601
So's this.

293
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:34,396
Well, considering my situation
and my back, just...

294
00:13:35,519 --> 00:13:36,398
continue.

295
00:13:38,103 --> 00:13:41,445
Kendra was about as irresponsible
as a person could be.

296
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:42,821
I told her,

297
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:44,850
after she paid her debt to me,

298
00:13:44,975 --> 00:13:46,805
she could spend her money
how she wanted.

299
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,082
Tough love.

300
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,330
- Did you give her a sword?
- A sword?

301
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,666
It's a knife, but it's only huge.

302
00:13:55,009 --> 00:13:55,834
No.

303
00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:58,681
But did you daughter mention
that she might've something of value?

304
00:13:58,806 --> 00:14:00,380
Because you'd take it away from her.

305
00:14:01,629 --> 00:14:04,092
- Okay, this doesn't work.
- Don't shut me off!

306
00:14:06,690 --> 00:14:09,639
I'd like to take a look
at your daughter's condo, Mr. Kim.

307
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:29,618
Looks like someone
really wanted that sword.

308
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:41,077
Precise slashes to the couch
and removal of ventilation

309
00:14:41,202 --> 00:14:43,797
screens suggests purpose
frustrated in the search.

310
00:14:43,922 --> 00:14:46,801
Digital answering machine
behind the bed. It's cracked.

311
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:49,221
See if Computer Forensics
can get anything off of it.

312
00:14:49,389 --> 00:14:51,181
Found some running shoes
in the closet.

313
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:53,517
Soles contain insects,
soil and blood.

314
00:14:53,685 --> 00:14:55,912
- You want our lab or yours?
- Yeah, mine.

315
00:14:56,037 --> 00:14:58,427
I'd like to see you try
and get these away from me now.

316
00:14:58,552 --> 00:15:00,106
Figuratively speaking, of course.

317
00:15:01,190 --> 00:15:02,567
Anything else, Dr. Hodgins?

318
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:04,903
In some ways,
you're just like Booth.

319
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:06,965
Mean that as a compliment.

320
00:15:07,090 --> 00:15:08,597
I don't think you do.

321
00:15:11,135 --> 00:15:12,077
Check this out.

322
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:15,525
Mandibular trauma downward,
maxillary trauma upward.

323
00:15:15,650 --> 00:15:18,225
Trauma to the molars
extends bilaterally.

324
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:21,945
The force radiated symmetrically
from the center of her mouth.

325
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:23,463
It's like her face exploded.

326
00:15:23,631 --> 00:15:25,960
Certainly nothing I've seen before.

327
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:29,145
Very good, Mr. Fisher.

328
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,270
Really?

329
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:34,570
Just seems like the truth is further
away than it was before

330
00:15:34,695 --> 00:15:36,601
and like laughing at us.

331
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:41,063
Process of elimination is a key
step to discovering the truth.

332
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:44,025
I've seen many
unusual murder weapons.

333
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:48,113
So the fact that I don't recognize
this one, rules out all the others.

334
00:15:49,903 --> 00:15:51,658
My kind of silver ling.

335
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,409
It's depressing.

336
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:03,135
The blood I found on the Booth
babe's running shoes... not human.

337
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:05,503
I think our princess kissed a toad.

338
00:16:06,841 --> 00:16:09,365
Bufo Americanus. American toad.

339
00:16:09,552 --> 00:16:11,695
- So she stepped on a frog?
- A toad.

340
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,910
Bufo Americanus.

341
00:16:13,035 --> 00:16:16,266
Which amphibian is down to
one local population

342
00:16:16,548 --> 00:16:17,433
right here

343
00:16:17,558 --> 00:16:18,756
near the Potomac

344
00:16:18,881 --> 00:16:22,855
in an area which matches the soil and
the flora found beneath her fingernails.

345
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:26,483
She went for a run, stepped on a frog,
and buried something.

346
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:29,988
A toad, and yeah, that's the picture
forming in my mind, too.

347
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:34,835
We pulled this message off
the victim's answering machine.

348
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,245
I don't know who you think
we're fooling, little princess,

349
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:39,728
but you're playing with a woman
who gets what she wants.

350
00:16:39,853 --> 00:16:42,631
You've got three days.
I want that sword.

351
00:16:44,693 --> 00:16:47,185
You want me to do a profile from
a voice on an answering machine?

352
00:16:47,310 --> 00:16:49,132
Give it a shot.
You're a smarty-pants.

353
00:16:49,994 --> 00:16:51,009
Okay, fine.

354
00:16:51,432 --> 00:16:53,869
"You're playing with a woman."
That suggests that the caller

355
00:16:53,994 --> 00:16:56,139
regards the victim
as a child in comparison.

356
00:16:56,330 --> 00:16:58,099
Okay, so, so what, an old woman?

357
00:16:58,270 --> 00:17:00,225
No, no, experientially.

358
00:17:00,350 --> 00:17:02,195
Probably in terms
of sexual experience.

359
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,905
So you're looking for
someone fairly promiscuous.

360
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:07,805
I think that she's already tried
to take the sword from a man,

361
00:17:07,930 --> 00:17:10,737
and now is truly annoyed that
she has to deal with a girl.

362
00:17:12,050 --> 00:17:14,082
The auctioneer is a man,

363
00:17:14,703 --> 00:17:18,286
and he evaluated the sword
before Kendra panicked and buried it.

364
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:24,514
I can assure you that this
is a clean and fair auction.

365
00:17:24,639 --> 00:17:26,490
We've been running this
auction for 15 years.

366
00:17:26,615 --> 00:17:28,672
Please answer the question,
Mr. Dorf.

367
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:29,585
"Derf."

368
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:31,893
Yes, I certified
and registered the item.

369
00:17:32,018 --> 00:17:34,504
I gave the consigner an option
to store it in our secure room.

370
00:17:34,629 --> 00:17:35,512
She declined.

371
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:38,745
Consigner has to give you
detailed contact information, right?

372
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:40,599
- They want to get paid.
- And sometimes

373
00:17:40,724 --> 00:17:43,403
you give that information to certain
parties interested in

374
00:17:43,528 --> 00:17:44,780
illegal pre-bidding?

375
00:17:44,905 --> 00:17:47,590
What? No, no.
Look, I told you before...

376
00:17:47,715 --> 00:17:49,117
Your pupils are constricted,

377
00:17:49,242 --> 00:17:51,240
- suggesting an increase in adrenaline.
- What?

378
00:17:51,365 --> 00:17:54,321
And the change in voice pitch
indicates increased pressure in the neck

379
00:17:54,446 --> 00:17:56,050
via the laryngeal prominence.

380
00:17:56,175 --> 00:17:58,201
- What, what are you saying?
- You're lying to us.

381
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:01,746
Kinesthesia is a clear indicator
of dissembling, Mr. Dorf.

382
00:18:02,107 --> 00:18:04,207
"Derf." But look...

383
00:18:04,430 --> 00:18:05,825
Do you recognize this voice?

384
00:18:05,950 --> 00:18:08,178
I don't know who you think
you're fooling, little princess,

385
00:18:08,303 --> 00:18:10,619
but you're playing with a
woman who gets what she wants.

386
00:18:10,744 --> 00:18:13,750
You've got three days.
I want that sword.

387
00:18:14,075 --> 00:18:15,844
Did that woman contact
you about the sword?

388
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,324
Yes, she did.

389
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:21,055
Her name is Valerie Daniels.
She's a medieval weapons collector.

390
00:18:21,261 --> 00:18:24,955
And you provided her with Kendra
Kim's address and phone number.

391
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:28,314
Every auction does private
pre-bids, and no one ever gets...

392
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:30,725
- Hurt?
- What? Wait a minute.

393
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:34,230
What about Excalibur? Did you find it?
Is it still going up for auction?

394
00:18:34,355 --> 00:18:37,795
Booth is right.
You're like a portable polygraph.

395
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:40,620
He didn't mean that in a good way,
though, did he?

396
00:18:45,394 --> 00:18:49,377
This is quite a collection of medieval
and fantasy weapons, Miss Daniels.

397
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:53,381
My parents call it a waste of my trust
fund, which is praise enough for me.

398
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:56,239
Seems like an unlikely
hobby for a young woman.

399
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:58,130
I like sharp edges.

400
00:18:58,255 --> 00:19:01,012
I like sharp against soft.

401
00:19:02,162 --> 00:19:04,750
- What do you like, Dr. Sweets?
- What?

402
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:07,180
Can you account for your
whereabouts Wednesday night?

403
00:19:07,305 --> 00:19:09,564
Yeah. I was somewhere
not killing Kendra Kim.

404
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:11,983
- That's what you wanted to know?
- It's not what I asked.

405
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:14,495
I was at the Immortal
Comics after-party.

406
00:19:14,843 --> 00:19:17,255
You can ask Dean Noveck,
the publisher.

407
00:19:17,650 --> 00:19:19,615
We slept together.
The sex was vanilla.

408
00:19:19,740 --> 00:19:21,451
At least I got an alibi
out of it, right?

409
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:24,162
You feel a need to be in control,
don't you, Miss Daniels?

410
00:19:24,428 --> 00:19:26,664
I'd like to control
you if you're up for it.

411
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:28,583
Oh, I assure you I'm not.

412
00:19:28,752 --> 00:19:32,485
And your attempt to regain
self-esteem through sexual intimidation

413
00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:36,131
will not repair the dysfunctional
relationship you had with your father.

414
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:39,805
Abandonment, abuse, indifference.

415
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:44,091
You are far more ripped under those
schoolboy duds than one would think,

416
00:19:44,972 --> 00:19:46,226
aren't you, Dr. Sweets?

417
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:49,675
Yes, but right now,
I'm more interested to hear

418
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:53,149
why you trashed Kendra's condo
after you didn't kill her.

419
00:19:53,318 --> 00:19:54,943
Her condo was trashed?

420
00:19:55,112 --> 00:19:58,447
They were looking for Excalibur.
That's what you wanted, right?

421
00:19:59,175 --> 00:20:00,556
I travel the world

422
00:20:00,681 --> 00:20:03,284
tracking down rare
and beautiful weapons.

423
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:07,205
I do research, I develop contacts,
I put in serious work.

424
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:09,720
Along comes this booth
babe with a famous sword

425
00:20:09,845 --> 00:20:11,895
thought to be lost for decades.

426
00:20:12,696 --> 00:20:14,838
- She didn't deserve it.
- But you deserved it.

427
00:20:15,006 --> 00:20:16,381
I asked her where she get it.

428
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:18,999
She said somebody dressed
as a black knight

429
00:20:19,329 --> 00:20:21,678
just gave it to her
on the first day of imagicon.

430
00:20:21,846 --> 00:20:24,597
Just walked up and presented
it to her as a gift.

431
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,349
She expected me to believe that?

432
00:20:28,340 --> 00:20:29,990
I didn't kill the girl.

433
00:20:30,607 --> 00:20:32,644
I just wanted the sword.

434
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:43,254
- Thanks for coming along.
- Yeah,

435
00:20:43,505 --> 00:20:45,076
Any chance to get some fresh air.

436
00:20:45,406 --> 00:20:47,977
Lone guy with a metal
detector in the bushes...

437
00:20:48,102 --> 00:20:49,247
Looks kind of creepy.

438
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:51,149
It is.
And I know you.

439
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:52,750
Oh, boy!

440
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:55,295
- Frog!
- Toad, not frog.

441
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:56,763
Bufo americanus.

442
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:59,308
And virginia nailwort.

443
00:21:00,371 --> 00:21:02,111
We're close to where
she buried the sword.

444
00:21:02,236 --> 00:21:03,586
Hold on a second.

445
00:21:05,448 --> 00:21:07,198
I got frequency response.

446
00:21:17,343 --> 00:21:18,343
Excalibur.

447
00:21:20,821 --> 00:21:23,990
I am the once-and-future king.

448
00:21:24,386 --> 00:21:26,284
Way to not be creepy.

449
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:38,938
That is not a toy, dr. Hodgins.

450
00:21:39,063 --> 00:21:40,893
It kind of is.
It's a movie prop.

451
00:21:41,018 --> 00:21:42,178
Stainless steel blade.

452
00:21:42,303 --> 00:21:43,968
That was new technology
for the time.

453
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:46,179
- Edge is dull, of course.
- May I see?

454
00:21:50,159 --> 00:21:51,872
It's badly balanced.

455
00:21:52,718 --> 00:21:54,145
The blade is warped.

456
00:21:54,514 --> 00:21:57,664
All of the prints on
the sword belong to Kendra Kim.

457
00:21:58,190 --> 00:22:01,069
- Could this be the murder weapon?
- She wasn't stabbed or slashed.

458
00:22:01,237 --> 00:22:04,113
The damage to her jaw is unique.
Wasn't from being struck with a sword.

459
00:22:04,421 --> 00:22:05,902
Is that the sword?

460
00:22:06,235 --> 00:22:07,235
Can i?

