some of the most barbaric in history.

464
00:22:19,345 --> 00:22:20,755
It's a line from Star Wars.

465
00:22:20,923 --> 00:22:21,923
Obi-wan Kenobi.

466
00:22:22,091 --> 00:22:23,876
What language is
that supposed to be?

467
00:22:24,001 --> 00:22:25,252
Why is he all excited?

468
00:22:25,377 --> 00:22:28,721
Finding this sword has given us
a unique advantage in this case.

469
00:22:29,309 --> 00:22:31,179
We now have what
the killer wants the most.

470
00:22:31,304 --> 00:22:33,685
It only makes sense that the
killer's gonna come after it again.

471
00:22:33,853 --> 00:22:35,627
Dr. Sweets wants to lay a trap.

472
00:22:35,752 --> 00:22:38,315
You said that the auctioneer
is no longer a suspect, correct?

473
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,316
So we lean on him
to fake the auction?

474
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:42,318
We can't auction off evidence.

475
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:44,362
Uh, I never thought of that.

476
00:22:44,692 --> 00:22:46,914
We could insert an undercover asset

477
00:22:47,039 --> 00:22:49,995
who outbids everyone for the item
no matter how high the price goes.

478
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:52,815
The auction's tomorrow. I don't have
time to set up that kind of operation.

479
00:22:52,940 --> 00:22:54,956
I'll do it.
You and Dr. Brennan

480
00:22:55,124 --> 00:22:58,126
have already been seen walking around
imagicon asking questions, right?

481
00:22:58,538 --> 00:23:01,462
Whereas I am an unknown quantity.

482
00:23:01,807 --> 00:23:02,964
An enigma.

483
00:23:03,132 --> 00:23:06,467
Who is this man bidding
so aggressively for excalibur?

484
00:23:06,788 --> 00:23:09,470
I'm confident
that if our killer is there,

485
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:11,472
this will provoke him
to reveal himself.

486
00:23:11,779 --> 00:23:13,433
I play the mystery bidder, you...

487
00:23:13,601 --> 00:23:15,566
observe the unsuspecting suspects

488
00:23:15,691 --> 00:23:17,478
via video feed in a separate room.

489
00:23:17,603 --> 00:23:19,453
Who's gonna run the camera?

490
00:23:20,632 --> 00:23:23,651
We need someone who blends in.

491
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:25,631
Someone who looks
like they belong there.

492
00:23:25,756 --> 00:23:27,655
